NBARLI is the number>0 of the line edges.

Attention:
This number is not signifient if the User gives
the function Taille_Ideale(x,y,z)
which specifies the wished length of edges around
the point of coordinates x,y,z.

Example:
DefFunc taille_ideale(x,y,z);
 defvar r2;
 r2=x*x+y*y;
 if r2>1.01 then
   taille_ideale=1;
 else
   if r2>=0.99 then
     taille_ideale=0.005;
   else
     taille_ideale=0.1;
   endif;
 endif;
EndFunc;
To obtain a regular mesh, it is recommend to give
a continuous function, with no quick large variations.
